1. EDINBURGH.

The stateliness and beauty ol Edinburgh are pertrayed with pride. Holyrood and the Castle form the extremes; the Parliament House and St. Giles' lill up the middle ol the picture, and the whole has lor centre the crown ol St. Giles'. Yet three other ol the towns have longer tributes. Another ol the same by John Johnston on Edinburgh is lound in Machenzie's Scottirls Writers, 11. p. 402.
